full_content.content: Common reasons your Maytag washer is not turning on
The most common reasons your Maytag washer is not turning on are a malfunctioning electronic control board, broken motor or an inoperative power supply board.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Maytag washers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Maytag washer

A malfunctioning electronic control board can lead to various failures in a washer. This is because the board serves as the brain of the washer, controlling crucial components such as the water valve, drive motor, drain pump, and cycles. If the electronic control board fails, the washer may not power up or display the cycle status. Additionally, it might fail to fill, agitate, spin, or drain. In some cases, a shorted board may emit a burning smell.
How to replace the electronic control board in a washer

A broken washer motor will prevent the spin basket from rotating or agitating, and can also cause a variety of other issues that affect the washer’s ability to function properly. Signs that the motor is wearing out include unusual noises during operation, such as grinding or squealing sounds. The washer may also exhibit erratic spinning or agitation, with clothes not being properly rinsed or still soaking wet after the spin cycle. Additionally, a worn-out motor may lead to the washer not completing its cycles, stopping abruptly, or not starting at all. Burnt smells or overheating around the motor area can be indicative of internal problems. In some cases, visible damage to the motor itself may be apparent.
How to replace the motor in a washer

If the power supply board is inoperative, the washer will not power up. This is because the power supply in a washer connects the incoming power from the cord to the components inside. A defective power supply may fail to protect the washer from power surges, potentially causing damage to electronic components like the electronic control board. If your washer is not powering up, it is recommended to have a Sears Home Services professional inspect it.
Why doesn't my washing machine work at all?
What to expect when you experience a Maytag washer not turning on issue
How is the not turning on problem fixed?

Correcting most not turning on problems usually involves replacing the electronic control board, motor or power supply. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a washer that is not turning on

When the washer is not turning on it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of washer failures.
What to look out for with a washer not turning on diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your washer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.
Maytag Washer Will Not Turn On Troubleshooting
Follow these basic troubleshooting steps when your Maytag washer will not turn on:
Check the power cord to make sure it is fully plugged into the electrical outlet. Plug in the power cord if you find it partially or fully unplugged.
Reset the house circuit breaker for the washing machine electrical outlet. This may restore power to the washer so you can power it up.
Check the electrical outlet for power by plugging a night light or small appliance into the outlet. If the electrical outlet is dead, have an electrician fix the electrical outlet.
If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help, a bad electronic control, faulty control panel or wiring failure could be the problem when your Maytag washer will not turn on.
Schedule washer repair service and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to your home to fix your Maytag washer that will not turn on.
Maytag Bravos XL Washer Will Not Turn On
When your Maytag Bravos XL washer will not turn on, use these expert troubleshooting tips to help you resolve the issue:
Make sure the power cord is plugged securely into the electrical outlet.
Check the house circuit breaker for the washer electrical outlet. Reset the house circuit breaker if you find it tripped.
Check the washing machine electrical outlet for power by plugging a night light or similar item into the outlet.
If the electrical outlet for your Maytag washer is dead, have an electrician fix that electrical outlet.

If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help, a bad electronic control board, defective control panel or wiring failure could be preventing your washing machine from powering up. Schedule washing machine repair services and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to visit your home and fix your Maytag Bravos XL washer that will not turn on.
How to Fix a Maytag Washing Machine that Won’t Turn On

When your Maytag washing machine won’t turn on and it has a timer, it can be difficult to know whether the washer is getting power. Check the power cord to make sure it’s plugged securely into the electrical outlet. Check the house circuit breaker for the washing machine electrical outlet and reset that house circuit breaker if you find it tripped.

If your Maytag washing machine still won’t turn on after resetting the house circuit breaker, unplug the washer power cord and check the electrical outlet for power. Plug a night light or similar item into the electrical outlet to check for power. If the electrical outlet is completely dead, have an electrician fix the outlet.

Make sure the lid is completely shut on the washer. Many Maytag washing machines won’t turn on if the lid is open. Check the lid strike and replace that part if it’s damaged. Check the mounting screws for the lid switch and tighten those screws if you find them loose.

If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help you fix your Maytag washing machine that won’t turn on, schedule washer repair service and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to your home to repair the washing machine.
Maytag Washer Locked and Won’t Turn On

When you find your Maytag washer locked and it won’t turn on, a power surge through the electrical lines may have affected the electronic control board. Resetting that control board may fix the problem. To reset the electronic control board in your Maytag washer, follow these steps:
Leave the power cord unplugged for 2 minutes.
Plug the power cord back into the electrical outlet to restore electrical power.
The electronic control board may reboot and your Maytag washer way begin working again. If not, perform these troubleshooting steps to ensure the washer has power:
Check the house circuit breaker for the washing machine outlet. Reset the house circuit breaker if you find it tripped.
Check the washer’s electrical outlet for power by plugging a night light or small lamp into the outlet.
If the electrical outlet is dead, have an electrician repair the electrical outlet.

If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help you resolve the problem with your Maytag washer locked and won’t turn on, schedule washer repair service and we’ll send a Sears Home Services technician to your home to fix the washing machine.
Maytag Washer Fills With Water Then Stops

When your Maytag washer fills with water then stops, check the lid to make sure it’s fully closed. Some top-load Maytag washing machines will fill with water but won’t start agitating if the lid is open. Also, check the lid strike and replace that part if it’s damaged. If the lid strike is okay, unplug the washer and check the lid switch mounting screws. Tighten those screws if they’re loose.

A problem with the water level pressure sensor can also be the problem when your Maytag washer fills with water then stops. Loose wiring or a failed contact in the water level pressure switch can prevent the washer from shifting into the agitation mode after filling.

If your Maytag washer that fills with water then stops has an electronic control board and control panel, resetting the electronic control board may fix the problem. Unplug the washer power cord for 2 minutes then plug the power cord back in. The washer may operate properly after the control board reboots.

If these basic troubleshooting tips don’t help you resolve the problem with your Maytag washer that fill with water then stops, schedule washer repair service to have a Sears Home Services technician fix the washing machine.

No response from a Maytag washer generally signals deeper electrical blockages—like a blown fuse or severed wiring harness. Simple resets won’t bypass these hardware failures. Instead of manual scrubbing, use a
. Power restoration ensures your Maytag can handle daily loads again.

full_content.content: Why won’t my Maytag washer turn on?
Check if the washer is plugged in, inspect the power cord for damage, and verify the door switch is functioning properly.
Could a malfunctioning door switch prevent my Maytag washer from turning on?
Yes, a broken door switch will stop the washer from turning on. Replace the switch to fix the issue.
How do I fix my Maytag washer if it’s not turning on?
Ensure the washer is plugged in, check the power cord, and inspect the door switch for faults.
What causes my Maytag washer to not turn on?
A faulty door switch, broken power cord, or malfunctioning control board can prevent the washer from turning on.

What is the drum of the washing machine?
The drum is the core part of the washer that holds your laundry and enables the cleaning process through rotation, agitation, and rinsing.
Hard water is water that contains high levels of dissolved minerals, particularly calcium and magnesium. It contrasts with soft water, which has lower concentrations of these minerals.
What is a Washing Machine Pedestal?
A washing machine pedestal is a platform that raises the washer off the ground, providing easier access to the appliances and often includes additional storage space such as drawers.

A washer tub is the interior part of a washing machine where clothes are placed for washing, typically made of stainless steel, plastic, or porcelain-coated metal, designed to hold water and withstand the agitation or spinning during the wash cycle.

Please note that your opt-out choice is specific to this website, browser, and device. If you access other Transformco websites, you will need to make your election for each. Also, if you clear your Cookies on this browser or use another browser or device, you may need to opt out again on this website.

Please note: Opting out may affect our ability to personalize your experience on this website, though we may use Cookies that do not include Sales, Sharing, or Targeted Advertising. You may still receive non-personalized advertisements on other sites or personalized ads that may be based on information processed before you opted out.

This website recognizes the Global Privacy Control (“GPC”), which is designed to recognize certain browser-based opt-out preference signals. We will process the GPC signal as a request to opt out. To process your request through GPC, you must use a browser or browser extension that supports the signal and turn it on for each browser and device you use.
